158
00:06:55,765 --> 00:06:58,435
and be a super-success
like Shaq.

159
00:06:58,537 --> 00:07:00,737
And you, Big Milhouse,
stop whining.

160
00:07:00,741 --> 00:07:02,551
Somebody calls
your family a loser,

161
00:07:02,545 --> 00:07:04,345
you stand up for yourself.

162
00:07:04,348 --> 00:07:06,148
I will.

163
00:07:06,152 --> 00:07:08,462
(inspirational music playing)

164
00:07:09,759 --> 00:07:12,599
<i>SKINNER:
On behalf of the school board,
I declare</i>

165
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:14,768
school is officially reopened.

166
00:07:14,769 --> 00:07:18,579
Let the free childcare and
intermittent learning resume.

167
00:07:18,677 --> 00:07:21,217
I'm here to officially protest
the teaching

168
00:07:21,215 --> 00:07:23,885
of the Great Springfield
Gazebo Disaster.

169
00:07:23,887 --> 00:07:26,287
It makes our children
hate our town

170
00:07:26,392 --> 00:07:28,302
and me hate myself.

171
00:07:28,396 --> 00:07:29,796
The Gazebo Disaster?

172
00:07:29,799 --> 00:07:32,969
But we plan to tread water
on that unit for months.

173
00:07:32,972 --> 00:07:34,242
We're doing two weeks

174
00:07:34,241 --> 00:07:37,151
on the substandard
metal bracing alone.

175
00:07:37,147 --> 00:07:38,317
Not anymore.

176
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:40,146
I demand that you ban

177
00:07:40,253 --> 00:07:42,863
Critical Brace Theory now.

178
00:07:42,959 --> 00:07:45,329
Sir, we're not changing
our curriculum

179
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:48,140
just to shore up
the wet cardboard lean-to

180
00:07:48,136 --> 00:07:50,406
that is your family self-esteem.

181
00:07:50,407 --> 00:07:52,337
Then you leave me one choice.

182
00:07:52,344 --> 00:07:54,424
Until you meet my demands,

183
00:07:54,415 --> 00:07:57,615
I'm going to play this trumpet,
on which

184
00:07:57,722 --> 00:08:00,932
I have no formal training.

185
00:08:00,928 --> 00:08:02,568
(dissonant playing)

186
00:08:02,665 --> 00:08:05,065
- Aah!
- Mr. Van Houten, if we,

187
00:08:05,170 --> 00:08:06,370
uh, if we could just...

188
00:08:06,372 --> 00:08:08,982
Look, there's no need
for brass instruments.

189
00:08:08,977 --> 00:08:11,977
For 30 years,
we've been pleading with parents

190
00:08:11,983 --> 00:08:13,493
to get more involved.

191
