Marge, stop saying things.

196
00:08:29,018 --> 00:08:31,188
I'm trying to think
of an amazing product

197
00:08:31,188 --> 00:08:32,988
that can get us out of debt.

198
00:08:33,092 --> 00:08:34,832
Uh... um...

199
00:08:34,829 --> 00:08:37,469
Handgun Underpants?
Mm, no.

200
00:08:37,467 --> 00:08:39,237
Uh, Bucket in a Box?

201
00:08:39,238 --> 00:08:41,478
Spoon 2.0?
Steak Bedazzler?

202
00:08:41,475 --> 00:08:42,775
Oh...

203
00:08:42,779 --> 00:08:44,979
(clears throat)
Yes, we are all here

204
00:08:44,983 --> 00:08:48,363
because one lone parent
raised an issue

205
00:08:48,456 --> 00:08:50,626
that he thinks
is worth me missing

206
00:08:50,628 --> 00:08:52,528
the new Equalizer starring

207
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:54,372
that delightful Queen Latifah.

208
00:08:54,468 --> 00:08:56,838
Kirk!
You, regrettably,

209
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:58,240
have the floor.

210
00:08:58,376 --> 00:08:59,646
We need to stop teaching

211
00:08:59,646 --> 00:09:03,516
that my great-grandfather's
gazebo was a disaster.

212
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:06,290
But it was,
and it was his fault.

213
00:09:06,392 --> 00:09:09,702
His dying words were, "My bad."

214
00:09:09,699 --> 00:09:11,499
So?
Why can't our kids learn

215
00:09:11,503 --> 00:09:13,543
about things that make
our town proud?

216
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,580
Like, how if you want
to make a right on red,

217
00:09:15,578 --> 00:09:17,518
it's usually not a problem.

218
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:20,315
Why do we have to focus
on the bad stuff?

219
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,760
(indistinct chatter)

220
00:09:22,759 --> 00:09:25,329
We completely disagree.

221
00:09:25,463 --> 00:09:29,343
It's essential that all of
Springfield's darkest chapters

222
00:09:29,338 --> 00:09:31,478
be taught: the monorail,

223
00:09:31,576 --> 00:09:32,776
Lady Gaga's visit,

224
00:09:32,779 --> 00:09:34,979
and the gazebo collapse.

225
00:09:34,983 --> 00:09:37,863
If our kids aren't made to feel
ashamed of the past,

226
00:09:37,855 --> 00:09:41,555
how will they learn
to be ashamed of the future?

227
00:09:41,563 --> 00:09:42,573
(indistinct chatter)

228
00:09:42,565 --> 00:09:43,925
Look at my son.

229
00:09:44,034 --> 00:09:46,444
You think he needs
to feel worse about himself

230
00:09:46,439 --> 00:09:49,309
than he already clearly does?
(grunts)

231
